  "biography_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">Eparchides of Oineis was a 4th-century BCE Athenian author, known only from a citation in the lexicographer Harpocration. His name identifies him as coming from the deme of Oineis, part of the Athenian tribe Oineis in northern Attica. No further biographical details survive.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">His sole attested work is <strong>On the Demes of Attica</strong>, a lost prose treatise cited by Harpocration for information on Athenian civic subdivisions.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">Eparchides was a minor Atthidographer, a chronicler of Attic local history and institutions. His work contributed specific details on Athenian deme organization, serving as a reference for later antiquarians, though its impact was far more limited than that of major figures in the tradition.</p>\n</div>",
